cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a deep neural network model for joint modeling Natural Language Understanding (NLU) and Dialogue Management (DM) in goal-driven dialogue systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses deep reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of LSTM and Deep Neural Networks also suggests the categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its model on a specific task, meeting room booking, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
